sentences: Ruby Lovett (born February 16, 1967 in Laurel, Mississippi) is an American country music singer-songwriter.
She cut a 45 rpm recording of "One Day at a Time" and "Me and Jesus" when she was 6 years old.

She later entered local talent contests and won the True Value Country Showdown three years in a row.
Lovett signed with Curb Records who released her debut album, Ruby Lovett, in January 1998.
